# gra architecture

## Philosophy

Keep it simple and changes minimal. Unless there is good reason, do not add new packages.

## Layering (do not blur)

- `cli.py` — Typer wiring only. Lazy-import `from . import data` inside commands.
- `data.py` — Public facade: re-export LVK API + non-LVK helpers (e.g. 2MASS). Stay thin.
- `data_lvk.py` — All LVK strain/PE/download/process logic.
- `plots.py` — Matplotlib only; no downloads or file discovery.
- `pe_lvk.py` — Event-name adapters only; delegate bilby/likelihood work to `likelihoodloader`.

## Call direction

CLI → `data` → `data_lvk` / `plots`
`pe_lvk` → `data_lvk` (paths) + `likelihoodloader` (PE/likelihood)

Never put LVK download logic in `cli.py` or `data.py`.
Never put bilby/likelihood building in `data_lvk.py` — that belongs in `likelihoodloader` via `pe_lvk.py`.

## On-disk layout (cwd-relative)

Per event `{event_name}/`:
- `{event}_{det}_strain.gwf`, `{event}_info.json`
- `official_pe/*.hdf5` (Zenodo PE)
- `{event}_{det}_noise_{before,after}.gwf`, `*_psd*.npy`, `*_strain.pdf`, `*_psd*.pdf`

New features must follow this cache-first, per-event folder pattern.

## Public API

User-facing functions live in `data.py` (re-exported from `data_lvk` where applicable).
Import as `gra.data`, `gra.data_lvk`, `gra.plots` — **not** from `gra` top-level.
Internal helpers use `_` prefix and stay in the owning module.

## `__init__.py` (critical)

- **No imports** in `src/gra/__init__.py` — docstring only.
- Never re-export `data`, `data_lvk`, `plots`, or their functions from `gra`.
- CLI autocomplete and `import gra` must stay lightning fast; heavy deps load only inside command handlers / submodule use.
